<item>
            <title>[LU-19506] Nodemap: ro flag for all matching filesets must be checked on mount</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19506</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When multiple filesets are configured that share a directory hierarchy, e.g.,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;1. &quot;/dir&quot;
2. &quot;/dir/subdir (ro)&quot; &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;whereby read-only is set for fileset 2, mounting subdirectory &quot;/lustre/dir/subdir&quot; only looks for a matching fileset. This could result in fileset 1 being matched which does not have ro flag set, resulting in an rw write mount which is incorrect. Instead, fileset matching should always consider the closest fileset at mount time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="93100">LU-19506</key>
            <summary>Nodemap: ro flag for all matching filesets must be checked on mount</summary>
